By Chibuike Nwabuko Abuja (Sundiata Post) -. Kuje prison is reportedly under attack and now in flames as residents are said to be in shock over endless sounds of gunshots. Residents of AA1 and Karimafo area of Kuje said that the jail break attempt started around 10:45pm on Tuesday when the gunshots started. The residents said at first they suspected it was robbery attack going on within their neighborhood and contacted the Kuje DPO who said his men have been deployed and that they are trying to find their way to know exactly how to access where it’s really happening and that they are doing there best. Sundiata Post gathered that military and other security agencies have been deployed to repel the attack and bring the situation to control. As at the time if filling this report, there is no confirmation from the authorities on the real situation of things as the calls put across to the DPO went through but he could not take his call. Details later…. By GAMI TADANYIGBE KUJE- Security has been tightened in most parts of Kuje communities in the Federal Capital Territory (FCT), following sporadic gunshots and bomb blast reportedly heard at the Kuje Correctional Centre on Tuesday night.Correspondent of the News Agency of Nigeria (NAN) who went round the area, observed heavy security… In "Metro" Abuja (Sundiata Post) - The suspended deputy commissioner of police, Abba Kyari, has been moved out of Kuje Prison after the terror attach on the facility. Several Inmates have escaped from Kuje Prisons following a Terror attack on the Facility on Wednesday night. The terrorists launched the attack around 10:30… In "Top Stories" Abuja (Sundiata Post) -. Bandits numbering over 20, have again, reportedly kidnapped a traditional ruler in Plateau State, His Royal Highness, Aminu Derwan, after attacking his palace in Panyam, Mangu Local Government Area of the state. It was learnt that the gunmen took away Derwan, the district head of Panyam,… In "News"